<DOC><DOCNO> AP890416-0014 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-16-89 1157EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-China-Quake     04-16 0333</FIRST><SECOND>AM-China-Quake,0342</SECOND><HEAD>Quake Rocks Southwest China; 4 Dead, 5 Injured</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A powerful earthquake destroyed 30 homes in aremote village in southwest China early Sunday, and an officialreport said at least four people were killed and five injured.   The exact number of casualties was not known becausecommunication with some towns in the area was broken, the state-runXinhua News Agency said.   The quake, which measured 6.7 on the Richter scale, struck at5:34 a.m. near the town of Batang, which is close to Sichuanprovince's western border with Tibet, the State SeismologicalBureau said.   Over the next seven hours, more than 1,000 aftershocks wererecorded, five measuring above 4 on the scale, Xinhua quotedprovincial scientists as saying.   The affected region of Sichuan is a densely populated ruralmountain region. Many of the residents are Tibetans. Populationfigures were not immediately available.   Xinhua said about 30 houses collapsed in Sangdagou village inZhubalong township, the epicenter of the quake. It said cracksappeared in 80 percent of the houses in nearby Batang.   A bridge on the Jinsha River, which passes through Batang, wasdamaged along with water conservation and power facilities, Xinhuasaid.   Premier Li Peng, who returned to Beijing on Sunday after afive-day visit to Japan, immediately was briefed on the earthquakeand sent Sichuan officials a message of sympathy, Xinhua said. Itsaid he urged them to take steps to minimize possible losses fromaftershocks and restore life to normal.   Xinhua said rescue teams were en route to the epicenter.   The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by anearthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on aseismograph. A quake measuring 6 or higher can cause severe damagein a populated area.   An earthquake measuring 7.6 killed 730 people and injured about4,000 in November in Yunnan province, south of Sichuan. It wasChina's worst earthquake since the 1976 temblor that leveled mostof the northeastern city of Tangshan.</TEXT></DOC>